; addams.scr 3/31/96

; ** Mad and Demetrius's Bar (beta)

; 621, room outside of Psycho's bar

NUMBER 621
NAME Teeth of Shartan, ledge
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
As you near the mid-point of the ladder an unusual sight is revealed.
A large cavernous room has been carved into the cliff wall itself. The
Southern side wall of the room faces the ladder and is completely
exposed. A small railing offers an easy climb into the room. A
sliding glass window protects patrons from the harsher elements when
needed. It is currently open. The room is pock marked with tables
and chairs and a large shape looms far within the darkened room. A
curious sign rests above you in a carved niche.
*DESCRIPTION_END
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
EXIT ABOVE 2112
ITEM 0 449 ADJ1=492
ITEM 1 449 ADJ1=493
ITEM 2 1112
ITEM 3 72 ADJ1=178 VAL2=3715

IFPREVERB EXAMINE 2
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER A skeleton stands above you in a niche carved into the rock face.
  ECHO PLAYER He endlessly pounds on a large steel block with a sledgehammer,
  ECHO PLAYER sending a reverberant 'CLANG' through the countryside. A coarsely
  ECHO PLAYER painted yellow sign blurts out the following message in red:%c
  ECHO PLAYER                   THE ANVIL:
  ECHO PLAYER             Come In And Get Hammered!
ENDIF

IFVERB GO 0
	ECHO PLAYER You'll have to climb that.
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFVERB GO 1
	ECHO PLAYER You'll have to climb that.
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFVERB CLIMB 0
	ECHO OTHERS %N climbs up the ladder.
	ECHO PLAYER You climb up the ladder.
	MOVE 622
	AFFECT 622
	ECHO OTHERS %N clambers onto the tiny ledge from below.
	AFFECT 621
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFVERB CLIMB 1
	ECHO OTHERS %N climbs down the ladder.
	ECHO PLAYER You climb down the ladder.
	MOVE 620
	AFFECT 620
	ECHO OTHERS %N steps off the ladder onto the precipice.
	AFFECT 621
	CLEARVERB
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
	IFVAR RAC ! 7
		ECHO PLAYER The strange cries of the wind send chills up your spine, when you pause.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR RAC = 7
		ECHO PLAYER You notice the wind causes the ladder to vibrate, thus creating sound.
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB JUMP -1
	IFVAR FLAG1 = 0
		ECHO PLAYER Do you really want to jump to your death.
		ECHO OTHERS %N looks as if %s wants to jump.
		EQUAL FLAG1 1
	ENDIF
	IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
		ECHO PLAYER You jump off!
		ECHO OTHERS %N jumps off!
		MOVE 620
		AFFECT 620
		RANDOM WHATANASS3 1 6 0
		MULT WHATANASS3 5
		POSITION LAY
		DAMAGEPLR CRUSH WHATANASS3 %N hits the ground with a thud.
		AFFECT 621
	ENDIF
ENDIF

; 3715-3717

NUMBER 3715
NAME Bar Room
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A saffron haze is cast over the bar by a chandelier bristling with hundreds
of candles. They give off an aroma of some unknown spice that trawls at
the back of your mind. The view out the open face of the bar stretches
forever, only hampered by the eyesight of the viewer. You can not help but
feel dwarfed by the immensity of the mountain surrounding you. Two midget
oaks stand witness at the entrance in honor of the foresters. A number of
tables are arranged eclectically throughout their rooms. Each table is
wedded to four chairs that never wander far from their mate. Goblins,
giants, ogres, kobolds, murgs, drakins and even humans are scattered
throughout the bar, all engaging in raucous laughter. Even the strange
patrons and magnificent view cannot detract your attention from the mammoth
bar dominating the far wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFENTRY
IFVAR INTNUM3 ! 1
 SPELL 406 100
 SPELL 250 100
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 294 ; Mad
    ECHO PLAYER As you walk up to the bar, Granite poors you a Hot & Cold.
    ECHO OTHERS As %n walks into the bar, Granite poors %i a drink.
    ECHO ALL Granite says, "Aye Tree Huga'. Lead anyon' ta thar deth's t'day?"
    NEWITEM 8 546
    NEWPUT 8 243 ADJ1=162 ADJ2=592 ADJ3=61
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 244 ; Heart
    ECHO PLAYER Granite smiles at you and pours you an ale.
    ECHO OTHERS Granite smiles at %n and pours %i an ale.
    NEWITEM 8 546
    NEWPUT 8 239
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 304 ; Demetrius
    ECHO PLAYER As you walk in, you see Granite poor you a wine.
    ECHO OTHERS As %n walks in, you see Granite poor %h a wine.
    ECHO ALL Granite exclaims, "Hearts ben ca'sin trouble agin Dem!"
    NEWITEM 8 546
    NEWPUT 8 237 ADJ1=468 ADJ2=353 VAL2=5
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 170 ; Brook
    ECHO PLAYER When you walk in, Granite pours you a water and point towards Fayd .
    ECHO OTHERS When %n walks in, Granite pours %i a water and points toward Fayd.
    ECHO ALL Granite excalims, "Hey Healer, BC's down that way!"
    NEWITEM 8 546
    NEWPUT 8 198
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 255 ; Saryon
    ECHO PLAYER When you walk in, Granite makes you an ice cold toddy.
    ECHO OTHERS When %n walks in, Granite makes %i an ice cold toddy.
    ECHO ALL Granite exclaims "Aye, there'll be no trouble 'n har t'day Sar'on!"
    NEWITEM 8
    NEWPUT 9 461 ADJ1=165 ADJ2=61 VAL2=5
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 319 ; Feather
    NEWITEM -1 274
    ECHO PLAYER Granite hands you a rose.
    ECHO OTHERS Granite hands %n a rose.
    ECHO ALL Granite says, "Compl'ments of Mad Mord'gan."
    NEWITEM -1 274 ADJ1=259
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM3 = 165 ; Gulbane
    ECHO PLAYER As you enter, the crowd seems to magically part, letting you through.
    ECHO OTHERS As Gulbane enters, the crowd seems to magically part, letting him through.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
ENDIF

ITEM 0 1342 ADJ1=189 ADJ2=693

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
The bar dominates the back quarter of the room. Spread out in a semicircle
it rises from the floor, a solid piece of the mountain itself. Masterful
Highlanders have left the solid stone intact as they carved the room around
it. The top has been leveled and polished smooth. Uncut gems of every
color jut from the bar, locked firmly within the stone. They glisten in
the candlelight, flicking quiet shards of colored light into the air. A
gruff Highlander is statued stoically behind the bar awaiting your order.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 1 204

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 1
Hot and Cold Grog         1 gold piece
Midnight Ale              2 gold pieces
Red Hot Mead              3 gold pieces
Deeplander Frappe         4 gold pieces
Ice Cold Toddy            5 gold pieces
Golden Wolfling Wine       6 gold pieces
White Goblin Brandy       8 gold pieces

Potions: Contact Mad, Demetrius or Marble--prices seasonal

[To order a drink, simply say the FULL name of the drink.
Ex: "Hot and Cold Grog"
Note: Do not use the BUY command]
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 2 202

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 2
This establishment is a neutral building. No Mining, stealing,
magic, or drawing of weapons allowed. Penalties are banishment
and general teasing from other occupants. In other words, go to
the test tunnels to pick on the kobolds. They have it rough
enough.
*DESCRIPTION_END

