ITEM 1 1306 ; map

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 1
This ancient topographic map seems to be of the undersea area outside
the windows. In the center of the map where you are now standing is a
drawing of what appears to be some sort of mining or drilling rig.
The detail drawing of the rig includes heavy equipment, storage and
crew quarters. Apparently Sirvak's dome is built on the same site
next to a section of coral reef.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 2 378 ADJ1=1261 ; blinking box

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
Multicolored tubes of some unknown fluid bubble throughout the mechanism of
this wonderous device. Thin black discs are stacked in rows behind a glass
panel and one of these discs sits flat on a rotating platform. A panel on
the front lists several song titles beside a numbered guide. The base of
the machine consists large speakers.
*DESCRIPTION_END

VARIABLE SIRVAKJUKEBOX

IFPREVERB POKE 2
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You punch your selection in on the numbered panel.
  ECHO OTHERS %n walks up to %a and makes a selection.
  EQUAL SIRVAKJUKEBOX 1
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL A new disc drops onto the platform and a tune starts to play.
ENDIF

VARIABLE SIRVAKCOUNT1

IFPREVERB LISTEN -1
  IFVAR SIRVAKCOUNT1 = 0
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You can hear nothing, the box seems to be off.
  ELSE
    IFVAR SIRVAKCOUNT1 < 120
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The various sliding pitches of hard rock and roll fills the room.
    ELSE
      IFVAR SIRVAKCOUNT1 < 240
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO ALL The booming sounds of a large ochestra fill the room!
      ELSE
        IFVAR SIRVAKCOUNT1 < 400
          CLEARVERB
          ECHO ALL A booming deep voice, mixed in with a sweet, high voice fill the room with
          ECHO ALL the sounds of an opera.
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF

