CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This large room takes up most the space in the small building. It is a
square room with a door on the south wall leading to the streets of Fayd.
On the north wall is an archway with a curtain hanging in it, concealing
the room beyond. The east and west walls each hold a window and below each
window is a bench. In the center of the room is a large mat woven from
reeds. The mat sits in front of a rough oak altar that is not polished,
nor impressive. Behind the altar, mounted on the wall is the only
extraordinary item in the building. It is a large mirror with a scene
etched in it's surface. The scene depicts a tired-looking elderly man
gathering apples and placing them in huge baskets hanging from a yoke slung
across his shoulders. Along the bottom edge of the mirror is the word
"Kaliban". Four large burning candles on the altar provide the only
illumination in the room.
*DESCRIPTION_END

