*DESCRIPTION_START
Stately best describes the foyer of the tower. Spacious and
magnificently decorated, the ceiling first catches your gaze.
The huge, vaulted ceiling is supported by intricately carved oak
beams. The flagstone floor is made up of interlocking white
marble, flecked with black pearl shards. Light from ornate brass
wall sconces, as well as the fireplace reflect off the burnished
granite wall. A painting hangs above the huge red brick
fireplace. A eastern facing window provides a glimpse of the
Foresters Grove. Pushed into a corner sits a rosewood roll-top
desk. To the west rests a finely crafted wooden table surrounded
by brown leather arm chairs. A stone stairway leads up, but it
is the sparkling fountain in the center of the room which holds
your attention.
