NUMBER 768
NAME Linnaeus' Tower
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
You step into a spacious, one-room loft at the top of a circular tower.
The walls seem oddly distant, yet the space itself seems finite. An
antique desk rests along one wall beneath a massive bookcase filled with
all manner of documents and books. Directly in the center of the room
rests a large comfortable sofa, facing an enormous picture window. You
notice a wooden arch built into one wall, but can not imagine where it
leads too.
*DESCRIPTION_END

