       ECHO PLAYER You see the dense gray mass of storm clouds hanging just outside your window.
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER Just below your gaze, the Fayd glows in a hazy illumination from a thousand tiny lights.
  ENDIF
ENDIF

; ** Locksmith (w/ key duplicator that breaks)

NUMBER 331
NAME Locksmith
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR

*DESCRIPTION_START
The shelves are lined with a number of chests and coffers. A few ominous
looking traps are also on display inside an glass case. The smiling
locksmith invites you to examine his wares and select the proper devices
for securing your valuables. A manuscript nailed to the wall describes the
different chests and traps available.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT O 247
ITEM 0 202
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 0
Chests         Lock        Price
------         ----        -----
Chest          Normal      40 Crowns
Coffer         Normal      30 Crowns
Strongbox      Superior   100 Crowns

Traps                Price
-----                -----
Poison Needle       20 Crowns
Black Needle        50 Crowns
Gas Vent           100 Crowns

Key duplication on ordinary keys, 50 crowns. Just place your key on the counter.
*DESCRIPTION_END

STOREITEM 88 -1 4000
STOREITEM 93 -1 3000
STOREITEM 98 -1 10000
STOREITEM 245 12 10000
STOREITEM 190 240 2000
STOREITEM 244 25 5000

IFSAY HELP
	ECHO ALL A clerk replies, "Just place they key you want duplicated onto the counter."
	ECHO ALL And with that, the clerk gestures to the counter that stands between you and
	ECHO ALL him.
ENDIF

IFSAY HELP?
	ECHO ALL A clerk replies, "Just place they key you want duplicated onto the counter."
	ECHO ALL And with that, the clerk gestures to the counter that stands between you and
	ECHO ALL him.
ENDIF

IFSAY KEY
	ECHO ALL A clerk replies, "Just place they key you want duplicated onto the counter."
	ECHO ALL And with that, the clerk gestures to the counter that stands between you and
	ECHO ALL him.
ENDIF

IFSAY KEYS
	ECHO ALL A clerk replies, "Just place they key you want duplicated onto the counter."
	ECHO ALL And with that, the clerk gestures to the counter that stands between you and
	ECHO ALL him.
ENDIF

IFSAY KEY?
	ECHO ALL A clerk replies, "Just place they key you want duplicated onto the counter."
	ECHO ALL And with that, the clerk gestures to the counter that stands between you and
	ECHO ALL him.
ENDIF

IFSAY KEYS?
	ECHO ALL A clerk replies, "Just place they key you want duplicated onto the counter."
	ECHO ALL And with that, the clerk gestures to the counter that stands between you and
	ECHO ALL him.
ENDIF

ITEM 1 720 ; counter

VARIABLE TEMPKEYVAL1
VARIABLE TEMPKEYVAL2
VARIABLE TEMPKEYVAL3
VARIABLE TEMPKEYVAL4
VARIABLE TEMPKEYVAL5

IFPREVERB2 PUT 1
  IFVAR ARCHNUM = 246
    IFVAR WEALTH > 4999
      SUB WEALTH 5000
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 15
      EQUAL TEMPKEYVAL1 ITEMVAL1
      EQUAL TEMPKEYVAL2 ITEMVAL2
      EQUAL TEMPKEYVAL3 ITEMVAL3
      EQUAL TEMPKEYVAL4 ITEMVAL4
      EQUAL TEMPKEYVAL5 ITEMVAL5
      NEWITEM 8 246 ADJ1=539
      SETITEMVAL 8 1 TEMPKEYVAL1
      SETITEMVAL 8 2 TEMPKEYVAL2
      SETITEMVAL 8 3 TEMPKEYVAL3
      SETITEMVAL 8 4 TEMPKEYVAL4
      SETITEMVAL 8 5 TEMPKEYVAL5
      GMMSG %n just made a key.
      ECHO PLAYER You pay the clerk.
      ECHO OTHERS %n pays the clerk.
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL %cThe clerk takes the key and places it in a machine along with a blank copy of the key.
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL The clerk then begins to grind away an exact match of the key.
      PLREVENT 2
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL The clerk finishes up and buffs the rough edges of the key down.
      PLREVENT 1
      CONTPLREVENT
      ECHO ALL The clumsy clerk goes to place the key back on the counter, and slips. The key
      ECHO ALL falls to the floor.
      ECHO ALL The clerk says, "Sorry about that! Please, come again", and returns to his work.
    ELSE
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER The clerk tells you that you can not afford to have a key duplicated.
      ECHO OTHERS The clerk tells %n that %s does not have enough money to make a copy of a key.
    ENDIF
  ELSE
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO ALL The clerk says, "Sorry, can't make a duplicate of that." and points to the manuscript.
  ENDIF
ENDIF


